1
00:00:01,472 --> 00:00:04,305
(MultiCom Jingle)

2
00:00:13,645 --> 00:00:16,645
(suspenseful music)

3
00:02:18,862 --> 00:02:23,029
(screaming)
(suspenseful music)

4
00:03:36,909 --> 00:03:41,076
(crickets chirping)
(dogs barking)

5
00:03:58,658 --> 00:03:59,918
- Well, of course no one really believes

6
00:03:59,918 --> 00:04:02,503
in the old Devil of the middle ages,

7
00:04:02,503 --> 00:04:04,760
with horns and a pitchfork.

8
00:04:04,760 --> 00:04:06,808
Anymore than people
really believe God looks

9
00:04:06,808 --> 00:04:08,598
like the old man painted on the ceiling

10
00:04:08,598 --> 00:04:10,345
of the Sistine Chapel.

11
00:04:10,345 --> 00:04:11,646
- My point exactly.

12
00:04:11,646 --> 00:04:12,479
Gin.

13
00:04:12,479 --> 00:04:14,396
- You win again Robert.

14
00:04:15,386 --> 00:04:17,276
- I don't question the
existence of evil Sam

15
00:04:17,276 --> 00:04:19,388
just of supernatural evil.

16
00:04:19,388 --> 00:04:21,176
- But if you believe in miracles--

17
00:04:21,176 --> 00:04:24,447
(doorbell ringing)

18
00:04:24,447 --> 00:04:26,114
- Who could that be?

19
00:04:28,465 --> 00:04:31,372
(doorbell ringing)

20
00:04:31,372 --> 00:04:32,574
Where is that girl?

21
00:04:32,574 --> 00:04:33,407
Kathryn?

22
00:04:35,931 --> 00:04:37,972
(doorbell ringing)

23
00:04:37,972 --> 00:04:39,381
That girl.

24
00:04:39,381 --> 00:04:40,798
Such a good girl.

25
00:04:46,669 --> 00:04:47,819
- Mrs. Grove?

26
00:04:47,819 --> 00:04:48,652
- Yes.

27
00:04:49,557 --> 00:04:52,261
- It's not that I don't believe
in Heaven you understand,

28
00:04:52,261 --> 00:04:54,323
it just that all the
most interesting people

29
00:04:54,323 --> 00:04:57,716
seems to me would end
up in the other place.

30
00:04:57,716 --> 00:04:58,780
- Oh Robert.

31
00:04:58,780 --> 00:04:59,613
- What?

32
00:05:01,095 --> 00:05:02,012
What is it?

33
00:05:03,535 --> 00:05:05,068
- Nothing.

34
00:05:05,068 --> 00:05:08,975
- Miss Lester what's your
opinion on the subject of Hell?

35
00:05:08,975 --> 00:05:10,788
Miss Lester?

36
00:05:10,788 --> 00:05:14,459
- I have no opinion on
the subject Mr. Delaney.

37
00:05:14,459 --> 00:05:18,120
- I think it must be a
very interesting place.

38
00:05:18,120 --> 00:05:20,570
- Excuse me everyone.

39
00:05:20,570 --> 00:05:23,460
I'd like for you all
to meet Mrs. Albright.

40
00:05:23,460 --> 00:05:25,547
She's going to be staying with us.

41
00:05:25,547 --> 00:05:26,687
- Hello.
- Hello.

42
00:05:26,687 --> 00:05:27,520
- [Miss Lester] Hello.

43
00:05:27,520 --> 00:05:28,726
- Oh here let me run it down for you,

44
00:05:28,726 --> 00:05:31,892
There's Miss Lester, she
teaches at the Oak Grove school.

45
00:05:31,892 --> 00:05:32,725
- [Miss Lester] Hi.

46
00:05:32,725 --> 00:05:33,813
- And there are the Delaneys,

47
00:05:33,813 --> 00:05:35,909
Mr. Delaney is in insurance.

48
00:05:35,909 --> 00:05:37,240
- We're pleased to meet you.

49
00:05:37,240 --> 00:05:38,073
- Thank you.

50
00:05:38,073 --> 00:05:39,974
- Oh and our bachelors,

51
00:05:39,974 --> 00:05:41,918
This is our young Mr. Reynolds,

52
00:05:41,918 --> 00:05:44,184
he's going to Boston tomorrow.

53
00:05:44,184 --> 00:05:47,184
- Ah, I have many friends in Boston.

54
00:05:48,106 --> 00:05:49,170
- Pleasure.

55
00:05:49,170 --> 00:05:50,404
- And this is our--

56
00:05:50,404 --> 00:05:52,714
- Our not so young Mr. Gray.

57
00:05:52,714 --> 00:05:55,078
You can call me Sam.

58
00:05:55,078 --> 00:05:57,078
Please, sit down Mrs. Albright.

59
00:05:57,078 --> 00:05:58,811
- Why thank you Sam.

60
00:05:58,811 --> 00:06:00,561
You may call me Lucy.

61
00:06:01,643 --> 00:06:03,037
- I'll do so frequently.

62
00:06:03,037 --> 00:06:04,367
(chuckles)

63
00:06:04,367 --> 00:06:06,678
- I'll have to watch out for you.

64
00:06:06,678 --> 00:06:09,937
- No need, he's all hot air that Sam Gray.

65
00:06:09,937 --> 00:06:12,520
So tell us Mrs. Albright, Lucy,

66
00:06:13,464 --> 00:06:16,596
What's your opinion on
the subject of the Devil?

67
00:06:16,596 --> 00:06:18,117
- The Devil?

68
00:06:18,117 --> 00:06:22,284
Well, he must be rather difficult
to be around I'd imagine.

69
00:06:24,112 --> 00:06:25,331
- Well there's an answer that doesn't

70
00:06:25,331 --> 00:06:27,855
leave much room for doubt.

71
00:06:27,855 --> 00:06:30,219
- The question is, do you actually believe

72
00:06:30,219 --> 00:06:32,613
the Devil is at work in the world today?

73
00:06:32,613 --> 00:06:34,495
Sending demons here and there?

74
00:06:34,495 --> 00:06:37,162
- Well that is quite a question.

75
00:06:39,508 --> 00:06:41,578
- Thank you for finally joining us.

76
00:06:41,578 --> 00:06:43,744
Didn't you hear the door ring?

77
00:06:43,744 --> 00:06:46,464
- No Aunt Mary I was in the kitchen.

78
00:06:46,464 --> 00:06:48,171
- Why is it that I never have any problem

79
00:06:48,171 --> 00:06:49,592
hearing the door from the kitchen

80
00:06:49,592 --> 00:06:53,972
but it always poses such
a challenge for you?

81
00:06:53,972 --> 00:06:55,945
- I don't know Aunt Mary.

82
00:06:55,945 --> 00:06:57,441
I'm sorry Aunt Mary.

83
00:06:57,441 --> 00:06:59,762
- Well we have a new guest.

84
00:06:59,762 --> 00:07:01,275
Get another cup please.

85
00:07:01,275 --> 00:07:03,390
Would you like tea or coffee?

86
00:07:03,390 --> 00:07:06,485
- [Mrs. Albright] Why tea
would be lovely thank you.

87
00:07:06,485 --> 00:07:09,068
- Don't just stand about go on.

88
00:07:10,361 --> 00:07:11,194
That girl.

89
00:07:12,407 --> 00:07:14,349
Oh, paper dolls.

90
00:07:14,349 --> 00:07:16,373
You know I used to cut
out paper dolls like that

91
00:07:16,373 --> 00:07:17,941
when I was a young girl.

92
00:07:17,941 --> 00:07:19,269
- Well I'm afraid paper dolls

93
00:07:19,269 --> 00:07:21,460
are all I can manage these days.

94
00:07:21,460 --> 00:07:23,043
The hands you know?

95
00:07:24,303 --> 00:07:25,878
- But it doesn't have a face.

96
00:07:25,878 --> 00:07:28,711
- Oh the face always goes on last.

97
00:07:29,595 --> 00:07:30,891
- The point I was trying to make

98
00:07:30,891 --> 00:07:35,058
is that if God has miracles
then Satan must too mustn't he?

99
00:07:35,941 --> 00:07:39,141
- I suppose you might be right.

100
00:07:39,141 --> 00:07:40,158
- The trouble is miracles aren't

101
00:07:40,158 --> 00:07:41,815
what they used to be are they?

102
00:07:41,815 --> 00:07:43,581
No voice from the heavens,

103
00:07:43,581 --> 00:07:46,768
no Red Seas parting,
no fire and brimstone.

104
00:07:46,768 --> 00:07:49,692
- Frankly, I think thou
dost protest too much,

105
00:07:49,692 --> 00:07:51,275
Mr. Reynolds is it?

106
00:07:53,249 --> 00:07:56,426
I think you really want to believe.

107
00:07:56,426 --> 00:07:58,288
- You're wrong Mrs. Albright,

108
00:07:58,288 --> 00:08:00,034
I want to know.

109
00:08:00,034 --> 00:08:01,330
There's a difference.

110
00:08:01,330 --> 00:08:04,311
- Well then I'll tell you what I think.

111
00:08:04,311 --> 00:08:07,195
If the Devil has one great power on Earth,

112
00:08:07,195 --> 00:08:10,005
it's the power to persuade men and women

113
00:08:10,005 --> 00:08:13,005
to do what they secretly want to do.

114
00:08:14,445 --> 00:08:16,048
- So be warned.

115
00:08:16,048 --> 00:08:17,391
- Yes.

116
00:08:17,391 --> 00:08:18,825
Fair warning.

117
00:08:18,825 --> 00:08:22,992
(chuckles)
(ominous music)

118
00:08:34,948 --> 00:08:37,615
(ominous music)

119
00:09:04,476 --> 00:09:07,809
(screaming and weeping)

120
00:09:26,041 --> 00:09:27,208
Where are you?

121
00:09:28,079 --> 00:09:29,579
Ah, there you are.

122
00:09:33,759 --> 00:09:35,676
Row impede, row impede,

123
00:09:37,610 --> 00:09:40,027
quickly bring me what I need.

124
00:09:41,514 --> 00:09:45,681
(ominous music)
(whimpering)

125
00:09:59,878 --> 00:10:00,711
Go.

126
00:11:11,732 --> 00:11:12,732
- She lives,

127
00:11:15,490 --> 00:11:17,417
she lives in the house.

128
00:11:17,417 --> 00:11:19,730
She lives in the house.

129
00:11:19,730 --> 00:11:21,480
He lives in the town.

130
00:11:22,482 --> 00:11:24,399
They live in the kitty?

131
00:11:27,410 --> 00:11:28,243
Kitty?

132
00:11:30,236 --> 00:11:31,426
(sighs)

133
00:11:31,426 --> 00:11:33,491
Kitty, kitty, kitty.

134
00:11:33,491 --> 00:11:34,324
Hell.

135
00:11:45,017 --> 00:11:47,387
- [Robert] I don't understand
what the problem is.

136
00:11:47,387 --> 00:11:49,151
It's perfectly simple,

137
00:11:49,151 --> 00:11:51,164
a five year old could do it.

138
00:11:51,164 --> 00:11:52,831
Monday is the pearl.

139
00:11:54,923 --> 00:11:55,782
Please say it.

140
00:11:55,782 --> 00:11:58,358
- [Both] Monday is the pearl.

141
00:11:58,358 --> 00:12:01,149
Tuesday the inlaid silver.

142
00:12:01,149 --> 00:12:03,128
Wednesday the bronze,

143
00:12:03,128 --> 00:12:04,461
and Thursday is.

144
00:12:05,514 --> 00:12:06,555
- Coat of arms.

145
00:12:06,555 --> 00:12:08,656
- The coat of arms.

146
00:12:08,656 --> 00:12:11,078
- [Both] Friday is polished silver.

147
00:12:11,078 --> 00:12:13,136
Saturday the tiger eye,

148
00:12:13,136 --> 00:12:14,803
and Sunday the gold.

149
00:12:15,952 --> 00:12:17,776
- [Robert] And today is what?

150
00:12:17,776 --> 00:12:19,109
- It's Thursday.

151
00:12:20,641 --> 00:12:22,687
- Then can you explain to me,

152
00:12:22,687 --> 00:12:27,261
why I had to go to work
today with the inlaid silver?

153
00:12:27,261 --> 00:12:29,103
Is this too much for you?

154
00:12:29,103 --> 00:12:31,150
Am I asking too much?

155
00:12:31,150 --> 00:12:33,825
Is this too much for you to handle?

156
00:12:33,825 --> 00:12:35,068
- It's just that we were late,

157
00:12:35,068 --> 00:12:38,373
I was late and rushed and I just forgot.

158
00:12:38,373 --> 00:12:40,833
- It's like living with a child.

159
00:12:40,833 --> 00:12:45,146
All I want in my life is a
tiny little bit of order.

160
00:12:45,146 --> 00:12:46,185
Just a bit.

161
00:12:46,185 --> 00:12:47,018
Something!

162
00:12:48,603 --> 00:12:50,723
I thought that I had married a woman,

163
00:12:50,723 --> 00:12:54,640
instead I discover that
I have married a child.

164
00:12:56,044 --> 00:12:58,032
Isn't that what you are?

165
00:12:58,032 --> 00:12:58,865
Isn't it?

166
00:13:00,437 --> 00:13:02,227
(sobbing)

167
00:13:02,227 --> 00:13:04,394
Yes, that's a good answer.

168
00:13:05,310 --> 00:13:06,643
Cry like a baby.

169
00:13:06,643 --> 00:13:07,555
Just cry!

170
00:13:07,555 --> 00:13:08,388
Please!

171
00:13:09,543 --> 00:13:11,210
- Robert I love you!

172
00:13:12,339 --> 00:13:13,237
- That's fine.

173
00:13:13,237 --> 00:13:16,874
That makes everything
all right doesn't it?

174
00:13:16,874 --> 00:13:19,624
(downbeat music)

175
00:14:12,663 --> 00:14:14,192
- Move on to the next,

176
00:14:14,192 --> 00:14:15,429
we won't be getting anything more

177
00:14:15,429 --> 00:14:17,429
out of Mr. Gray tonight.

178
00:14:42,899 --> 00:14:45,732
(shaky breathing)

179
00:14:51,877 --> 00:14:52,710
- Okay now remember,

180
00:14:52,710 --> 00:14:55,190
no amount of belief makes a fact.

181
00:14:55,190 --> 00:14:56,704
The world wasn't one less bit round

182
00:14:56,704 --> 00:14:59,981
when everyone believed it was flat was it?

183
00:14:59,981 --> 00:15:02,795
The question isn't whether
we believe in a God,

184
00:15:02,795 --> 00:15:04,772
but whether there really is one.

185
00:15:04,772 --> 00:15:07,130
(shaky breathing)

186
00:15:07,130 --> 00:15:08,047
Am I right?

187
00:15:09,533 --> 00:15:11,790
- Yes Mr. Reynolds,

188
00:15:11,790 --> 00:15:14,207
we'll have to start with you.

189
00:15:15,079 --> 00:15:18,079
(mischievous music)

190
00:15:19,366 --> 00:15:22,033
(ominous music)

191
00:16:18,941 --> 00:16:21,191
(knocking)

192
00:16:37,011 --> 00:16:37,879
- [Will] Mrs. Albright?

193
00:16:37,879 --> 00:16:41,599
- I'm very very sorry to
wake you Mr. Reynolds.

194
00:16:41,599 --> 00:16:42,682
- It's uh ...

195
00:16:44,012 --> 00:16:45,162
What's wrong?

196
00:16:45,162 --> 00:16:47,419
- It's my luggage you see.

197
00:16:47,419 --> 00:16:48,420
- Excuse me?

198
00:16:48,420 --> 00:16:50,099
- The men brought it from the station

199
00:16:50,099 --> 00:16:51,661
and it's piled up outside.

200
00:16:51,661 --> 00:16:53,442
I didn't want to wake anybody,

201
00:16:53,442 --> 00:16:54,288
but I'm afraid I--

202
00:16:54,288 --> 00:16:55,205
- That's...

203
00:16:56,758 --> 00:16:58,023
- Would you mind?

204
00:16:58,023 --> 00:17:00,606
- No, no just give me a minute.

205
00:17:02,111 --> 00:17:03,778
- Thank you so much.

206
00:17:13,801 --> 00:17:14,747
- There.

207
00:17:14,747 --> 00:17:15,580
All set.

208
00:17:16,469 --> 00:17:17,639
Now if you'll excuse me I have to get up

209
00:17:17,639 --> 00:17:19,757
very early in the morning.

210
00:17:19,757 --> 00:17:21,522
- Mr. Reynolds?

211
00:17:21,522 --> 00:17:23,855
What would you give to know?

212
00:17:25,604 --> 00:17:26,865
- Excuse me?

213
00:17:26,865 --> 00:17:29,106
- What would you give to know?

214
00:17:29,106 --> 00:17:32,417
Really know, that's there's a God,

215
00:17:32,417 --> 00:17:35,084
a Devil, a life beyond this one.

216
00:17:37,876 --> 00:17:39,198
- Well, my bank account's a little slim

217
00:17:39,198 --> 00:17:40,352
right now Mrs. Albright.

218
00:17:40,352 --> 00:17:43,802
- You think I'm making
clever conversation.

219
00:17:43,802 --> 00:17:44,635
I'm not.

220
00:17:45,650 --> 00:17:47,704
What would you give me
if I could prove say,

221
00:17:47,704 --> 00:17:49,454
that demons are real.

222
00:17:50,495 --> 00:17:52,162
What would you give?

223
00:17:53,038 --> 00:17:54,621
If I could do that?

224
00:17:55,754 --> 00:17:56,788
(sighs)

225
00:17:56,788 --> 00:17:58,474
- Mrs. Albright.

226
00:17:58,474 --> 00:18:01,895
- Wouldn't it be worth just
about anything to know?

227
00:18:01,895 --> 00:18:02,728
For sure?

228
00:18:03,794 --> 00:18:04,794
- I suppose.

229
00:18:05,865 --> 00:18:07,747
- Is it a deal then?

230
00:18:07,747 --> 00:18:09,227
- I'm sorry?

231
00:18:09,227 --> 00:18:12,538
- Will you give me anything I ask for?

232
00:18:12,538 --> 00:18:16,121
If I can prove to you
that demons are real?

233
00:18:17,108 --> 00:18:18,624
- Why not?

234
00:18:18,624 --> 00:18:20,761
Anything you want.

235
00:18:20,761 --> 00:18:22,474
If you can convince me,

236
00:18:22,474 --> 00:18:24,557
but I'm hard to convince.

237
00:18:27,316 --> 00:18:28,281
What's that?

238
00:18:28,281 --> 00:18:29,548
- Ivy leaf

239
00:18:29,548 --> 00:18:31,783
It keeps the noise from leaving the room.

240
00:18:31,783 --> 00:18:34,232
We don't want to disturb the others do we?

241
00:18:34,232 --> 00:18:35,197
- I don't know.

242
00:18:35,197 --> 00:18:37,171
Why not let everyone in on it?

243
00:18:37,171 --> 00:18:40,171
- No no, tonight is just between us.

244
00:18:51,135 --> 00:18:53,440
Mr. Reynolds, would you help me unbutton

245
00:18:53,440 --> 00:18:55,773
the back of my dress please?

246
00:18:57,035 --> 00:18:59,250
- Now Mrs. Albright.

247
00:18:59,250 --> 00:19:01,420
- Oh please, do you really think

248
00:19:01,420 --> 00:19:04,389
I intend something improper?

249
00:19:04,389 --> 00:19:07,064
- Well, I mean no but...

250
00:19:07,064 --> 00:19:08,821
- Then come over here.

251
00:19:08,821 --> 00:19:11,071
I wanna show you something.

252
00:19:12,981 --> 00:19:13,814
Come come.

253
00:19:18,507 --> 00:19:20,596
Undo the back of my dress please.

254
00:19:20,596 --> 00:19:23,263
(ominous music)

255
00:19:41,099 --> 00:19:41,932
- What the?

256
00:19:41,932 --> 00:19:44,469
- Unlace the stitches would you please?

257
00:19:44,469 --> 00:19:45,302
- I'm sorry?

258
00:19:45,302 --> 00:19:47,166
- Unlace the stitches.

259
00:19:47,166 --> 00:19:49,916
(dramatic music)

260
00:20:20,001 --> 00:20:22,418
You know what I am don't you?

261
00:20:24,416 --> 00:20:25,249
- Yes.

262
00:20:37,171 --> 00:20:40,004
- So I've convinced you haven't I?

263
00:20:42,083 --> 00:20:42,916
- Yes.

264
00:20:47,111 --> 00:20:48,944
Oh God please help me.

265
00:20:50,471 --> 00:20:53,304
- No no no, you made your bargain.

266
00:20:55,918 --> 00:20:58,259
You know what you might've had,

267
00:20:58,259 --> 00:21:01,018
and you know what you've lost.

268
00:21:01,018 --> 00:21:01,851
Come.

269
00:21:06,119 --> 00:21:06,952
No, crawl.

270
00:21:16,159 --> 00:21:16,992
Closer.

271
00:21:18,779 --> 00:21:21,529
Now you must give me what I want.

272
00:21:22,729 --> 00:21:24,082
Your hand please.

273
00:21:24,082 --> 00:21:27,082
(suspenseful music)

274
00:21:38,831 --> 00:21:41,498
(pained groans)

275
00:22:06,761 --> 00:22:09,566
You may struggle if you like.

276
00:22:09,566 --> 00:22:12,760
It won't make any difference.

277
00:22:12,760 --> 00:22:15,093
(screaming)

278
00:22:22,327 --> 00:22:24,994
(clock ticking)

279
00:22:36,061 --> 00:22:37,376
- Why I can't understand it.

280
00:22:37,376 --> 00:22:39,796
He must've left early before breakfast.

281
00:22:39,796 --> 00:22:40,757
- It's strange.

282
00:22:40,757 --> 00:22:43,638
I was up early, I didn't hear him go.

283
00:22:43,638 --> 00:22:46,281
- Well he's not here
now so he must've left.

284
00:22:46,281 --> 00:22:49,173
- He told me he was going
to take an early train.

285
00:22:49,173 --> 00:22:50,495
- Really?

286
00:22:50,495 --> 00:22:54,328
Didn't know there were
any trains before noon.

287
00:23:03,334 --> 00:23:06,164
- My goodness you're as
nervous as a jumping bean.

288
00:23:06,164 --> 00:23:07,493
- I'm sorry ma'am, can
I get you something?

289
00:23:07,493 --> 00:23:10,177
- Oh no no I just wanted a cup of tea.

290
00:23:10,177 --> 00:23:12,019
No sit honey sit.

291
00:23:12,019 --> 00:23:13,740
- I'm sorry ma'am I'm sorry.

292
00:23:13,740 --> 00:23:15,254
Oh that's all right.

293
00:23:15,254 --> 00:23:16,421
- Dammit!

294
00:23:16,421 --> 00:23:17,550
I'm sorry.

295
00:23:17,550 --> 00:23:19,152
- Don't be silly.

296
00:23:19,152 --> 00:23:21,001
I've heard much worse.

297
00:23:21,001 --> 00:23:23,062
Here let me see.

298
00:23:23,062 --> 00:23:25,562
Oh it's nothing but a scratch.

299
00:23:28,297 --> 00:23:31,464
Well now my, isn't that interesting.

300
00:23:31,464 --> 00:23:32,562
- Ma'am?

301
00:23:32,562 --> 00:23:34,145
- Your palm, may I?

302
00:23:36,635 --> 00:23:38,556
You know you can learn a
great deal about someone

303
00:23:38,556 --> 00:23:40,473
by studying their palm.

304
00:23:41,496 --> 00:23:43,679
- I went to a gypsy once.

305
00:23:43,679 --> 00:23:46,679
She said I'd get rich, but I didn't.

306
00:23:47,848 --> 00:23:51,026
- I see you've been keeping a secret.

307
00:23:51,026 --> 00:23:51,859
- A secret?

308
00:23:51,859 --> 00:23:53,370
- Mmm Hmm.

309
00:23:53,370 --> 00:23:54,370
Right there.

310
00:23:55,434 --> 00:23:56,517
In your room.

311
00:23:59,158 --> 00:24:01,825
Why, you don't know how to read.

312
00:24:02,804 --> 00:24:04,304
- I can read fine.

313
00:24:06,975 --> 00:24:08,927
- I've hurt your feelings I'm sorry,

314
00:24:08,927 --> 00:24:10,510
don't be like that.

315
00:24:11,512 --> 00:24:14,845
Would you like to know a secret of mine?

316
00:24:15,688 --> 00:24:16,855
I'll tell you.

317
00:24:19,656 --> 00:24:23,823
I was older than you are
now when I learned to read.

318
00:24:25,228 --> 00:24:26,646
- Really?

319
00:24:26,646 --> 00:24:28,056
- Yes.

320
00:24:28,056 --> 00:24:29,306
It wasn't easy.

321
00:24:30,314 --> 00:24:32,231
- I know, sometimes ...

322
00:24:35,239 --> 00:24:39,406
- You'd like to be like other
young girls wouldn't you?

323
00:24:40,459 --> 00:24:42,457
- Smart like them you mean.

324
00:24:42,457 --> 00:24:43,290
Yes.

325
00:24:46,182 --> 00:24:50,349
- When I was young I wanted so
much to be like other girls,

326
00:24:53,544 --> 00:24:54,794
but I was slow.

327
00:24:59,409 --> 00:25:02,242
They'd laugh at me behind my back.

328
00:25:03,267 --> 00:25:05,017
Sometimes to my face.

329
00:25:06,267 --> 00:25:08,849
- I know, I hear 'em.

330
00:25:08,849 --> 00:25:12,461
I'd do just about anything to be able to

331
00:25:12,461 --> 00:25:13,878
not be so stupid.

332
00:25:17,144 --> 00:25:19,727
- If that's the way you really feel,

333
00:25:19,727 --> 00:25:21,777
then I can help you.

334
00:25:21,777 --> 00:25:24,444
Is that the way you really feel?

335
00:25:25,479 --> 00:25:27,078
- Yes ma'am.

336
00:25:27,078 --> 00:25:31,245
Sometimes I see a smart
girl talking about things,

337
00:25:32,940 --> 00:25:36,690
talking smart to men
and I wish I could just,

338
00:25:38,113 --> 00:25:40,733
I don't know I wish I could just kill her

339
00:25:40,733 --> 00:25:43,400
and steal her smarts for myself.

340
00:25:48,035 --> 00:25:50,952
- Would you like to know my secret?

341
00:25:51,946 --> 00:25:52,946
- Yes ma'am.

342
00:25:55,440 --> 00:25:57,869
- It's a special book.

343
00:25:57,869 --> 00:26:00,036
I always carry it with me.

344
00:26:03,640 --> 00:26:05,625
- The words are too big.

345
00:26:05,625 --> 00:26:07,566
