346
00:26:07,566 --> 00:26:08,733
- Yes you can.

347
00:26:10,177 --> 00:26:11,177
Concentrate.

348
00:26:12,609 --> 00:26:13,942
Look at it hard.

349
00:26:15,030 --> 00:26:16,530
You can read them.

350
00:26:22,132 --> 00:26:26,299
- A Concise and Illustrated
history of The Earth King.

351
00:26:29,993 --> 00:26:31,160
Why I read it.

352
00:26:32,159 --> 00:26:33,076
Every word.

353
00:26:34,344 --> 00:26:35,177
- Take it.

354
00:26:36,088 --> 00:26:36,921
Read it.

355
00:26:37,875 --> 00:26:39,708
I know you'll like it.

356
00:26:40,757 --> 00:26:44,074
- Kathryn have you finished
the silverware yet?

357
00:26:44,074 --> 00:26:45,685
- I'm afraid I was bothering her.

358
00:26:45,685 --> 00:26:47,228
- Oh no problem.

359
00:26:47,228 --> 00:26:50,048
Kathryn knows the work she's to do.

360
00:26:50,048 --> 00:26:52,922
Don't bother with that there's
a spill in the sitting room.

361
00:26:52,922 --> 00:26:54,020
Well go on!

362
00:26:54,020 --> 00:26:55,209
Get some rags.

363
00:26:55,209 --> 00:26:56,042
Hurry up.

364
00:27:25,751 --> 00:27:27,567
- [Robert] Gin.

365
00:27:27,567 --> 00:27:28,662
- You win again.

366
00:27:28,662 --> 00:27:31,264
- Yes, what's the point
in even playing with you?

367
00:27:31,264 --> 00:27:33,055
Would anyone else care for a game?

368
00:27:33,055 --> 00:27:34,202
Mr. Gray?

369
00:27:34,202 --> 00:27:35,702
- Oh no thank you.

370
00:27:36,759 --> 00:27:40,692
- Miss Lester, would you care to play?

371
00:27:40,692 --> 00:27:41,775
Cards I mean.

372
00:27:43,703 --> 00:27:44,953
- No thank you.

373
00:27:46,652 --> 00:27:48,235
I'll say goodnight.

374
00:27:53,991 --> 00:27:56,408
- I think I'll go to bed too.

375
00:27:58,462 --> 00:28:01,412
- A strange thing Mrs. Albright.

376
00:28:01,412 --> 00:28:02,607
- What's that?

377
00:28:02,607 --> 00:28:04,516
- I remember what you
said about Will Reynolds

378
00:28:04,516 --> 00:28:06,558
