400
00:32:08,929 --> 00:32:11,262
(screaming)

401
00:32:17,600 --> 00:32:19,164
- What?

402
00:32:19,164 --> 00:32:20,328
What?

403
00:32:20,328 --> 00:32:21,596
Wait, oh sweet Jesus.

404
00:32:21,596 --> 00:32:22,628
My wife, you'll wake the whole house.

405
00:32:22,628 --> 00:32:24,672
(shushing)

406
00:32:24,672 --> 00:32:25,505
What's wrong?

407
00:32:25,505 --> 00:32:27,600
(squealing)

408
00:32:27,600 --> 00:32:29,352
My God what's the matter with you?

409
00:32:29,352 --> 00:32:30,185
(screaming)

410
00:32:30,185 --> 00:32:31,380
No, no no no no, don't!

411
00:32:31,380 --> 00:32:32,325
Don't do this to me!

412
00:32:32,325 --> 00:32:33,161
(shushing)

413
00:32:33,161 --> 00:32:34,154
What did I do?

414
00:32:34,154 --> 00:32:34,987
Stop!

415
00:32:34,987 --> 00:32:35,820
Stop!

416
00:32:39,133 --> 00:32:41,776
(gunshot)

417
00:32:41,776 --> 00:32:44,109
(screaming)

418
00:32:46,179 --> 00:32:49,512
(gasping and screaming)

419
00:32:55,570 --> 00:32:57,070
- Oh, my goodness.

420
00:32:57,960 --> 00:32:59,197
What's happened?

421
00:32:59,197 --> 00:33:01,947
- He, he, he tried to assault me.

422
00:33:02,807 --> 00:33:03,640
Oh my God.

423
00:33:03,640 --> 00:33:05,890
(shushing)

424
00:33:08,244 --> 00:33:10,129
- Go back to your room.

425
00:33:10,129 --> 00:33:10,962
- Call the police.

426
00:33:10,962 --> 00:33:12,434
We have to call the police.

427
00:33:12,434 --> 00:33:14,402
- No it's all right.

428
00:33:14,402 --> 00:33:16,733
Go back to your room.

429
00:33:16,733 --> 00:33:19,316
We don't wanna wake the others.

430
00:33:21,264 --> 00:33:23,764
- But the shot and I screamed.

431
00:33:24,736 --> 00:33:25,958
- It's all right.

432
00:33:25,958 --> 00:33:26,791
Go on.

433
00:33:29,054 --> 00:33:31,101
- But he's still inside.

434
00:33:31,101 --> 00:33:32,684
- I'll be with you.

435
00:33:33,851 --> 00:33:36,163
(shushing)

436
00:33:36,163 --> 00:33:38,830
(ominous music)

437
00:34:17,907 --> 00:34:19,407
Ah, there you are.

438
00:34:24,147 --> 00:34:25,388
- That woman.

439
00:34:25,388 --> 00:34:28,787
That woman is insane she shot me!

440
00:34:28,787 --> 00:34:32,149
- He came into my room
he tried to assault me!

441
00:34:32,149 --> 00:34:33,954
He tore my nightgown!

442
00:34:33,954 --> 00:34:35,228
- She invited me!

443
00:34:35,228 --> 00:34:37,717
She's flirted with me
ever since she got here!

444
00:34:37,717 --> 00:34:40,390
She invited me, she gave me
the key and then she shot me

445
00:34:40,390 --> 00:34:41,803
because she's insane.

446
00:34:41,803 --> 00:34:43,186
- You!

447
00:34:43,186 --> 00:34:45,077
You despicable thing!

448
00:34:45,077 --> 00:34:46,279
- Oh God!

449
00:34:46,279 --> 00:34:47,112
Oh God.

450
00:34:48,020 --> 00:34:51,803
- Miss Lester, I think we
should move Mr. Delaney

451
00:34:51,803 --> 00:34:54,636
out of your room, don't you agree?

452
00:34:57,874 --> 00:35:00,624
Now do you think you can help me?

453
00:35:04,146 --> 00:35:05,896
- Let me get my robe.

454
00:35:10,424 --> 00:35:14,135
- Mr. Delaney, we're going
to walk you to my room.

455
00:35:14,135 --> 00:35:15,468
- Don't move me.

456
00:35:16,915 --> 00:35:20,748
Do you really want your
wife to find you here?

457
00:35:23,362 --> 00:35:24,695
Then come along.

458
00:35:34,705 --> 00:35:38,622
Let's sit him down at
the edge of the bed here.

459
00:35:40,779 --> 00:35:43,206
Now Miss Lester, go back to your room.

460
00:35:43,206 --> 00:35:45,638
- But the police, but we have to call them

461
00:35:45,638 --> 00:35:47,736
and what can I do?
- Miss Lester,

462
00:35:47,736 --> 00:35:49,486
go back to your room.

463
00:35:57,410 --> 00:36:01,122
(groaning in pain)

464
00:36:01,122 --> 00:36:03,289
- Please, call the doctor.

465
00:36:10,632 --> 00:36:14,192
- Mr. Delaney, you might as well know,

466
00:36:14,192 --> 00:36:17,677
at the rate you're bleeding
you'll be dead in a few minutes.

467
00:36:17,677 --> 00:36:20,103
All a doctor will be able to do

468
00:36:20,103 --> 00:36:22,486
is sign your death certificate.

469
00:36:22,486 --> 00:36:24,282
- Ah Christ!

470
00:36:24,282 --> 00:36:25,777
She gave me the key.

471
00:36:25,777 --> 00:36:27,716
I swear I didn't try to assault her.

472
00:36:27,716 --> 00:36:29,383
Please, get my wife.

473
00:36:31,166 --> 00:36:33,358
- Do you want to die?

474
00:36:33,358 --> 00:36:34,447
- What?

475
00:36:34,447 --> 00:36:36,709
- Do you want to die Mr. Delaney?

476
00:36:36,709 --> 00:36:38,968
- What are you talking about
you just told me that--

477
00:36:38,968 --> 00:36:42,232
- Isn't this a shocking waste?

478
00:36:42,232 --> 00:36:44,982
Wouldn't you like another chance.

479
00:36:46,076 --> 00:36:47,449
- What?

480
00:36:47,449 --> 00:36:49,810
- Wouldn't you do anything
if I could make that

481
00:36:49,810 --> 00:36:51,477
bullet hole go away?

482
00:36:52,627 --> 00:36:56,544
If I could heal you, if
I could save your life,

483
00:36:57,875 --> 00:37:00,124
what would it be worth to you?

484
00:37:00,124 --> 00:37:01,352
- My life?

485
00:37:01,352 --> 00:37:03,519
You're as crazy as she is.

486
00:37:05,417 --> 00:37:06,417
- Roll over.

487
00:37:07,284 --> 00:37:08,255
- What?

488
00:37:08,255 --> 00:37:10,543
- You don't believe me I'll show you.

489
00:37:10,543 --> 00:37:13,441
Roll over onto your side.

490
00:37:13,441 --> 00:37:16,358
(groaning in pain)

491
00:37:30,825 --> 00:37:33,009
- What in God's name are you doing?

492
00:37:33,009 --> 00:37:36,009
(liquid squelching)

493
00:37:43,151 --> 00:37:45,093
- That's got the bleeding stopped.

494
00:37:45,093 --> 00:37:45,926
Look.

495
00:37:48,139 --> 00:37:49,510
- What did you do?

496
00:37:49,510 --> 00:37:53,149
- Just wound back the bleeding a bit.

497
00:37:53,149 --> 00:37:54,654
- But it still hurts.

498
00:37:54,654 --> 00:37:56,681
- The bullet is still in there.

499
00:37:56,681 --> 00:37:58,767
It has to come out.

500
00:37:58,767 --> 00:38:00,698
Do you want me to take it out?

501
00:38:00,698 --> 00:38:02,656
- Yes of course!

502
00:38:02,656 --> 00:38:05,406
- Well then, what'll you give me?

503
00:38:06,670 --> 00:38:08,067
- I don't know.

504
00:38:08,067 --> 00:38:10,504
All I have, anything.

505
00:38:10,504 --> 00:38:12,421
I'll give you anything.

506
00:38:13,386 --> 00:38:14,724
- Good.

507
00:38:14,724 --> 00:38:16,141
Lie still please.

508
00:38:33,343 --> 00:38:36,176
(yelling in pain)

509
00:38:49,672 --> 00:38:51,422
- What is that thing?

510
00:38:52,968 --> 00:38:54,784
- What this?

511
00:38:54,784 --> 00:38:58,367
I suppose it's just
some kind of a fashion.

512
00:38:59,675 --> 00:39:01,137
- A fashion?

513
00:39:01,137 --> 00:39:02,793
- Yes a fashion.

514
00:39:02,793 --> 00:39:06,832
If I offered to cure you by
making passes over your stomach,

515
00:39:06,832 --> 00:39:08,776
or by shaking a corn rattle,

516
00:39:08,776 --> 00:39:11,859
