526
00:39:52,512 --> 00:39:53,854
No one wants to look straight

527
00:39:53,854 --> 00:39:56,437
into the eye of the impossible.

528
00:40:17,328 --> 00:40:18,745
- That's amazing.

529
00:40:19,900 --> 00:40:21,094
How did you do that?

530
00:40:21,094 --> 00:40:23,011
- Lie back down please.

531
00:40:25,053 --> 00:40:27,470
(whimpering)

532
00:40:34,624 --> 00:40:36,957
(screaming)

533
00:40:39,753 --> 00:40:41,732
(gasps)

534
00:40:41,732 --> 00:40:44,149
(whimpering)

535
00:40:56,961 --> 00:40:59,211
(knocking)

536
00:41:03,217 --> 00:41:04,800
- Mrs. Delaney, I--

537
00:41:05,829 --> 00:41:09,519
- I cleaned up all the
blood in the hallway.

538
00:41:09,519 --> 00:41:11,143
- Your husband, he--

539
00:41:11,143 --> 00:41:12,511
- I know what he did.

540
00:41:12,511 --> 00:41:14,299
We've got to get this place cleaned up.

541
00:41:14,299 --> 00:41:16,708
Do you have a clean sheet, a blanket?

542
00:41:16,708 --> 00:41:17,740
- What?

543
00:41:17,740 --> 00:41:19,352
- Help me, all the sheets and blankets,

544
00:41:19,352 --> 00:41:21,037
everything with blood on it.

545
00:41:21,037 --> 00:41:24,120
We'll clean up the carpet afterwards.

546
00:41:26,736 --> 00:41:29,238
- I don't understand.

547
00:41:29,238 --> 00:41:30,758
- Do what I tell you.

548
00:41:30,758 --> 00:41:33,076
Unless you want to go to jail.

549
00:41:33,076 --> 00:41:34,263
- Jail?

550
00:41:34,263 --> 00:41:35,518
- You know how the world works.

551
00:41:35,518 --> 00:41:36,797
What are the police?

552
00:41:36,797 --> 00:41:37,749
Men.

553
00:41:37,749 --> 00:41:39,409
The judges?

