Men.

555
00:41:40,429 --> 00:41:41,997
The juries?

556
00:41:41,997 --> 00:41:43,418
Ah, men!

557
00:41:43,418 --> 00:41:46,301
What do you think they'll believe?

558
00:41:46,301 --> 00:41:47,718
- What can we do?

559
00:41:50,474 --> 00:41:53,198
- Well no one else
knows but Mrs. Albright,

560
00:41:53,198 --> 00:41:54,781
and she won't tell.

561
00:41:56,023 --> 00:41:59,190
My husband is going to cease to exist.

562
00:42:00,143 --> 00:42:01,143
- Oh my God!

563
00:42:02,177 --> 00:42:04,967
- Robert's still alive
but he won't be for long.

564
00:42:04,967 --> 00:42:06,448
When we're done here
we'll carry him outside

565
00:42:06,448 --> 00:42:08,593
into the woods behind the house.

566
00:42:08,593 --> 00:42:09,883
Tomorrow morning I'll call the police

567
00:42:09,883 --> 00:42:11,272
and tell them that he went out for a walk

568
00:42:11,272 --> 00:42:13,046
and never came back.

569
00:42:13,046 --> 00:42:17,662
We'll make it look like he
was surprised by a thief.

570
00:42:17,662 --> 00:42:20,857
- How can you speak about it so calmly?

571
00:42:20,857 --> 00:42:22,512
- Speak about it?

572
00:42:22,512 --> 00:42:25,790
I've been dreaming about
something like this for years!

573
00:42:25,790 --> 00:42:29,630
Ever since I realized the
filthy thing I'd married.

574
00:42:29,630 --> 00:42:31,503
The plans were already there.

575
00:42:31,503 --> 00:42:35,510
I just needed something like
this to bring them to life.

576
00:42:35,510 --> 00:42:36,847
Get undressed.

577
00:42:36,847 --> 00:42:37,680
- What?

578
00:42:38,987 --> 00:42:41,582
- Look at you, you're covered in blood.

579
00:42:41,582 --> 00:42:42,675
Get undressed!

580
00:42:42,675 --> 00:42:45,840
Put your clothes over there with the rest.

581
00:42:45,840 --> 00:42:49,340
Unless you want the police to undress you.

582
00:42:52,065 --> 00:42:53,364
Don't.

583
00:42:53,364 --> 00:42:55,512
Your robe's covered in blood.

584
00:42:55,512 --> 00:42:58,179
Put it over there with the rest.

585
00:42:59,092 --> 00:43:00,166
Go over to the dresser.

586
00:43:00,166 --> 00:43:01,804
I need to clean you off.

587
00:43:01,804 --> 00:43:02,637
Hurry up.

588
00:43:12,396 --> 00:43:13,739
No time to be shy.

589
00:43:13,739 --> 00:43:15,000
We've got to be close.

590
00:43:15,000 --> 00:43:16,716
Close as sisters.

591
00:43:16,716 --> 00:43:18,883
- I've never had a sister.

592
00:43:22,181 --> 00:43:23,808
Is it bloody on my back?

593
00:43:23,808 --> 00:43:25,664
- It's everywhere.

594
00:43:25,664 --> 00:43:26,997
Did he hurt you?

595
00:43:28,106 --> 00:43:30,189
- He tore my night dress.

596
00:43:32,307 --> 00:43:33,474
He touched me.

597
00:43:35,186 --> 00:43:36,815
Touched me.

598
00:43:36,815 --> 00:43:37,982
- Turn around.

599
00:43:45,815 --> 00:43:46,898
- I'll do it.

600
00:43:56,230 --> 00:43:57,647
I'm sorry, sorry!

601
00:43:58,830 --> 00:44:00,863
- Is that what you want?

602
00:44:00,863 --> 00:44:01,696
- No!

603
00:44:01,696 --> 00:44:04,279
I didn't know what I was doing.

604
00:44:05,378 --> 00:44:06,963
- I've spent the last 10 years rehearsing

605
00:44:06,963 --> 00:44:09,463
my husband's death in my mind.

606
00:44:10,327 --> 00:44:12,943
What have you been rehearsing in yours?

607
00:44:12,943 --> 00:44:16,367
What do you think about
when you're all alone?

608
00:44:16,367 --> 00:44:17,200
- Nothing.

609
00:44:18,112 --> 00:44:20,054
- What are you afraid of?

610
00:44:20,054 --> 00:44:23,283
We're going to be murderers together.

611
00:44:23,283 --> 00:44:24,700
What do you want?

612
00:44:32,296 --> 00:44:34,545
This is what you want isn't it?

613
00:44:34,545 --> 00:44:35,378
Isn't it?

614
00:44:36,484 --> 00:44:37,317
- Yes.

615
00:44:37,317 --> 00:44:38,773
- More than anything?

616
00:44:38,773 --> 00:44:39,750
- Yes.

617
00:44:39,750 --> 00:44:43,936
- Then you'll do anything, anything I ask?

618
00:44:43,936 --> 00:44:45,420
- Yes.

619
00:44:45,420 --> 00:44:47,670
- Will you be mine forever?

620
00:44:49,384 --> 00:44:50,217
- Yes.

621
00:44:54,825 --> 00:44:57,492
(ominous music)

622
00:45:12,821 --> 00:45:14,966
- Do you think he's still alive?

623
00:45:14,966 --> 00:45:16,383
- Are you afraid?

624
00:45:21,557 --> 00:45:23,974
- It's too late to be afraid.

625
00:45:29,589 --> 00:45:32,422
- Oh it's never too late for that.

626
00:45:35,259 --> 00:45:37,926
(ominous music)

627
00:45:41,443 --> 00:45:43,860
(whimpering)

628
00:46:22,059 --> 00:46:22,892
- Robert?

629
00:46:30,663 --> 00:46:32,163
Are you all right?

630
00:46:33,914 --> 00:46:35,747
- Ellen I'm not blind.

631
00:46:36,970 --> 00:46:40,122
I know what I am, I know
that I'm not a good man.

632
00:46:40,122 --> 00:46:41,442
- [Ellen] That's not true.

633
00:46:41,442 --> 00:46:45,609
- I know that I haven't treated
you the way that I should,

634
00:46:47,193 --> 00:46:49,137
but it's not gonna go on.

635
00:46:49,137 --> 00:46:50,926
We're gonna break out of this life.

636
00:46:50,926 --> 00:46:54,535
We're gonna have a home
and servants and children.

637
00:46:54,535 --> 00:46:58,283
We're gonna have the life that we deserve.

638
00:46:58,283 --> 00:46:59,748
- We are?

639
00:46:59,748 --> 00:47:03,389
- And you are gonna have the
husband that you deserve,

640
00:47:03,389 --> 00:47:05,303
but we're gonna need courage.

641
00:47:05,303 --> 00:47:07,463
Do you have courage?

642
00:47:07,463 --> 00:47:09,139
- I don't know.

643
00:47:09,139 --> 00:47:10,667
I thought I did once but I just--

644
00:47:10,667 --> 00:47:12,932
- Ellen, look at me.

645
00:47:12,932 --> 00:47:15,368
I'm not a good man, I'm
weak and I'm vindictive,

646
00:47:15,368 --> 00:47:16,845
and I don't know how to love anything.

647
00:47:16,845 --> 00:47:18,178
Not even myself.

648
00:47:20,369 --> 00:47:21,619
Do you love me?

649
00:47:22,507 --> 00:47:25,113
- Yes Robert, you know I do.

650
00:47:25,113 --> 00:47:27,946
I've never wanted anything
more than your love.

651
00:47:27,946 --> 00:47:30,644
- I promise you nothing do you hear me?

652
00:47:30,644 --> 00:47:34,811
Knowing that, will you
still do what I ask of you?

653
00:47:35,918 --> 00:47:36,751
- Yes.

654
00:47:38,638 --> 00:47:40,152
- No questions?

655
00:47:40,152 --> 00:47:41,641
- No.

656
00:47:41,641 --> 00:47:43,468
- Anything for me?

657
00:47:43,468 --> 00:47:45,635
- Just tell me what to do.

658
00:47:47,064 --> 00:47:49,814
- Mrs. Grove has no bank account.

659
00:47:57,993 --> 00:48:00,368
- Are you sure there isn't
anything I can do for you?

660
00:48:00,368 --> 00:48:02,462
- No no, I'll be all right.

661
00:48:02,462 --> 00:48:04,138
- Should I send Kathryn
up with the powder?

662
00:48:04,138 --> 00:48:07,080
- No thank you Mrs. Grove,
I'm just going to lie down.

663
00:48:07,080 --> 00:48:08,423
- All right.

664
00:48:08,423 --> 00:48:10,161
- I'll try get home a bit early.

665
00:48:10,161 --> 00:48:12,161
- I'm sure I'll be fine.

666
00:48:17,962 --> 00:48:21,152
- Mr. Delaney, where did
you say that Mr. Gray went?

667
00:48:21,152 --> 00:48:22,183
- Something about trying to find

668
00:48:22,183 --> 00:48:24,431
Miss Lester and Mrs. Albright.

669
00:48:24,431 --> 00:48:26,325
Honestly I didn't quite understand him.

670
00:48:26,325 --> 00:48:27,342
See you this evening.

671
00:48:27,342 --> 00:48:29,842
- Have a good day Mr. Delaney.

672
00:48:30,700 --> 00:48:32,033
Oh, Mr. Delaney?

673
00:48:32,911 --> 00:48:33,816
- Hmm?

674
00:48:33,816 --> 00:48:35,816
- Did you hurt yourself?

675
00:48:36,773 --> 00:48:39,245
- Oh, no I just slept on it or something.

676
00:48:39,245 --> 00:48:40,078
Good day.

677
00:49:02,204 --> 00:49:03,960
- Oh good morning Mrs. Grove.

678
00:49:03,960 --> 00:49:04,982
- Well good morning.

679
00:49:04,982 --> 00:49:06,278
We missed you at breakfast.

680
00:49:06,278 --> 00:49:07,957
- Well I needed some help with some things

681
00:49:07,957 --> 00:49:10,230
and Miss Lester was very accommodating.

682
00:49:10,230 --> 00:49:12,563
(chuckling)

683
00:49:18,618 --> 00:49:20,555
Mrs. Grove, I was wondering

684
00:49:20,555 --> 00:49:23,042
if you might be able to help me.

685
00:49:23,042 --> 00:49:23,946
- Oh well I don't--

686
00:49:23,946 --> 00:49:27,547
- You see I just have no
head at all for money.

687
00:49:27,547 --> 00:49:28,576
- For money?

688
00:49:28,576 --> 00:49:29,409
- Yes.

689
00:49:29,409 --> 00:49:31,206
That's where Miss Lester
took me this morning,

690
00:49:31,206 --> 00:49:33,011
to see a man at the bank?

691
00:49:33,011 --> 00:49:36,594
You see Albert my dear
husband, he left me,

692
00:49:37,452 --> 00:49:40,657
what are those things called?

693
00:49:40,657 --> 00:49:41,490
Pillories.

694
00:49:42,596 --> 00:49:43,846
No, um, stocks!

695
00:49:45,157 --> 00:49:46,690
(laughter)

696
00:49:46,690 --> 00:49:49,193
That's it, yeah I have
quite a few of them,

697
00:49:49,193 --> 00:49:51,015
and this man at the bank well he said

698
00:49:51,015 --> 00:49:53,450
I should put them in some
sort of box at the bank.

699
00:49:53,450 --> 00:49:55,273
That I should put all
my money in the bank,

700
00:49:55,273 --> 00:49:57,094
but I don't know.

701
00:49:57,094 --> 00:49:58,808
- No you should think twice.

702
00:49:58,808 --> 00:50:01,908
Banks fold you know ,and
then all your money is gone.

703
00:50:01,908 --> 00:50:03,621
- Yes exactly.

704
00:50:03,621 --> 00:50:06,204
You see, you know all about it!

705
00:50:07,244 --> 00:50:08,994
So I was wondering...

706
00:50:12,058 --> 00:50:13,267
- Yes?

707
00:50:13,267 --> 00:50:15,522
- Could you advise me?

708
00:50:15,522 --> 00:50:17,554
I don't want to impose but it would take

709
00:50:17,554 --> 00:50:19,656
such a burden off of me if only someone

710
00:50:19,656 --> 00:50:22,823
would just take care of it all for me.

711
00:50:25,313 --> 00:50:27,407
- It would be a burden of course,

712
00:50:27,407 --> 00:50:31,574
but I know how it is being
widowed and all myself.

713
00:50:34,373 --> 00:50:37,318
I'd have to have free hand.

714
00:50:37,318 --> 00:50:38,666
- Oh of course.

715
00:50:38,666 --> 00:50:42,249
Of course I'd never
dream of taking charge.

716
00:50:44,413 --> 00:50:46,086
Are you busy right now?

717
00:50:46,086 --> 00:50:49,120
I could show you what I have in my trunk.

718
00:50:49,120 --> 00:50:52,897
Perhaps you could make some
sense out of it all for me.

719
00:50:52,897 --> 00:50:55,296
- Oh I'm not doing anything really.

720
00:50:55,296 --> 00:50:58,242
I could spend a few moments.

721
00:50:58,242 --> 00:50:59,753
- Thank you so much.

722
00:50:59,753 --> 00:51:02,420
(ominous music)

723
00:51:16,992 --> 00:51:18,606
No, this isn't right.

724
00:51:18,606 --> 00:51:20,736
I'm just taking advantage of you.

725
00:51:20,736 --> 00:51:22,026
You know what I'm going to do?

726
00:51:22,026 --> 00:51:24,034
I'm going to put all my money in the bank.

727
00:51:24,034 --> 00:51:25,256
I mean everyone does it.

728
00:51:25,256 --> 00:51:27,092
- Now now now don't do that,

729
00:51:27,092 --> 00:51:29,397
it's no bother for me really.

730
00:51:29,397 --> 00:51:30,734
- No I've made up my mind.

731
00:51:30,734 --> 00:51:33,345
Why should I push my troubles onto you.

732
00:51:33,345 --> 00:51:35,497
- Now no, now I insist.

733
00:51:35,497 --> 00:51:38,185
If you feel that you're taking advantage,

734
00:51:38,185 --> 00:51:40,685
well we'll work something out.

735
00:51:43,662 --> 00:51:44,945
- Are you certain?

736
00:51:44,945 --> 00:51:46,370
- Absolutely.

737
00:51:46,370 --> 00:51:48,407
I want to do this.

738
00:51:48,407 --> 00:51:50,231
We'll make an accommodation.

739
00:51:50,231 --> 00:51:53,231
Something that's fair to both of us.

740
00:51:54,158 --> 00:51:55,908
- Well I do want to be fair.

741
00:51:55,908 --> 00:51:58,098
(laughter)

742
00:51:58,098 --> 00:51:58,931
All right.

743
00:52:00,488 --> 00:52:02,655
We'll, how did you put it?

744
00:52:04,299 --> 00:52:06,632
We'll make an accommodation.

745
00:52:14,796 --> 00:52:15,629
- [Mrs. Grove] Are you telling me

746
00:52:15,629 --> 00:52:17,689
that you actually went to the police?

747
00:52:17,689 --> 00:52:19,524
- You're darn right I did.

748
00:52:19,524 --> 00:52:21,854
When Miss Lester didn't
show up at her classroom,

749
00:52:21,854 --> 00:52:23,480
and no one's seen her since,

750
00:52:23,480 --> 00:52:25,253
and there's no sign of
Will Reynolds either

751
00:52:25,253 --> 00:52:27,426
of course I went to the police.

752
00:52:27,426 --> 00:52:29,349
For all the good it did me.

753
00:52:29,349 --> 00:52:31,556
- Well, what did they say?

754
00:52:31,556 --> 00:52:34,756
- That they didn't have
sufficient grounds for action.

755
00:52:34,756 --> 00:52:38,906
That they couldn't declare
them missing for 48 hours.

756
00:52:38,906 --> 00:52:42,453
- And Mrs. Albright is missing too.

757
00:52:42,453 --> 00:52:46,133
- I swear I think there's something,

758
00:52:46,133 --> 00:52:49,315
something ungodly going on in this house.

759
00:52:49,315 --> 00:52:51,603
- Well as soon as Mr.
Delaney gets home from work

760
00:52:51,603 --> 00:52:53,273
I'm going to lock the door.

761
00:52:53,273 --> 00:52:54,593
Mrs. Albright comes home later,

762
00:52:54,593 --> 00:52:58,791
she won't be able to get
in without waking someone.

763
00:52:58,791 --> 00:53:00,570
- I'm going to my room.

764
00:53:00,570 --> 00:53:03,420
If she does come back,
or Miss Lester does,

765
00:53:03,420 --> 00:53:07,054
please wake me no matter what the hour.

766
00:53:07,054 --> 00:53:08,221
- Don't worry.

767
00:53:09,798 --> 00:53:14,437
Mrs. Albright won't be
murdering us in our beds.

768
00:53:14,437 --> 00:53:16,563
- I hope you're right.

769
00:53:16,563 --> 00:53:18,444
Good evening.

770
00:53:18,444 --> 00:53:20,444
- Good evening Mr. Gray.

771
00:53:28,519 --> 00:53:32,394
Oh Kathryn, as soon as
you're done cleaning up

772
00:53:32,394 --> 00:53:34,052
please go to your room.

773
00:53:34,052 --> 00:53:35,385
- Yes Aunt Mary.

774
00:53:37,337 --> 00:53:38,867
Aunt Mary?

775
00:53:38,867 --> 00:53:39,869
- Yes?

776
00:53:39,869 --> 00:53:42,532
- Did you hurt yourself?

777
00:53:42,532 --> 00:53:45,260
- Stick to your business.

778
00:53:45,260 --> 00:53:47,927
(ominous music)

779
00:54:15,230 --> 00:54:17,647
(whimpering)

780
00:54:25,695 --> 00:54:27,195
- Robert, I was...

781
00:54:33,011 --> 00:54:34,459
I was so afraid, it's so late!

782
00:54:34,459 --> 00:54:36,713
- There were things I had to take care of.

783
00:54:36,713 --> 00:54:38,713
Things I had to arrange.

784
00:54:39,735 --> 00:54:41,612
Are you ready?

785
00:54:41,612 --> 00:54:42,666
- Yes.

786
00:54:42,666 --> 00:54:44,709
- For anything?

787
00:54:44,709 --> 00:54:46,160
- I don't understand.

788
00:54:46,160 --> 00:54:50,789
- Listen carefully, Mrs.
Grove is in the sitting room.

789
00:54:50,789 --> 00:54:53,651
I'm going to go there
and keep her occupied.

790
00:54:53,651 --> 00:54:57,818
While I do, you have to go to
her room and get the money.

791
00:55:00,243 --> 00:55:01,175
- But I don't--

792
00:55:01,175 --> 00:55:03,226
- Do you love me?

793
00:55:03,226 --> 00:55:04,434
- [Ellen] Yes.

794
00:55:04,434 --> 00:55:07,767
- Then don't ask questions, just listen.

795
00:55:09,239 --> 00:55:14,154
There's a small table in
the corner on the far wall.

796
00:55:14,154 --> 00:55:16,611
There's a straight razor on top of it.

797
00:55:16,611 --> 00:55:20,349
Take the blade and slide it
along the top edge of the drawer

798
00:55:20,349 --> 00:55:23,379
until you hit a hidden catch.

799
00:55:23,379 --> 00:55:27,046
Open the drawer, our
money is hidden inside.

800
00:55:28,480 --> 00:55:32,755
Take it and put back everything
the way you found it.

801
00:55:32,755 --> 00:55:35,505
Lock the door and go to our room.

802
00:55:38,945 --> 00:55:40,362
- [Ellen] I will.

803
00:55:42,597 --> 00:55:45,938
- You know that everything
depends on this?

804
00:55:45,938 --> 00:55:50,206
If you fail, it would mean
prison for both of us.

805
00:55:50,206 --> 00:55:51,578
- I won't fail.

806
00:55:51,578 --> 00:55:53,406
- You'll do whatever you have to do?

807
00:55:53,406 --> 00:55:57,082
- Anything, I will do anything for you.

808
00:55:57,082 --> 00:55:59,158
- Here's the key.

809
00:55:59,158 --> 00:56:01,408
Wait five minutes, then go.

810
00:56:06,531 --> 00:56:07,364
Quietly.

811
00:56:12,201 --> 00:56:15,201
(suspenseful music)

812
00:57:00,392 --> 00:57:02,392
(gasps)

813
00:57:04,661 --> 00:57:07,182
- I thought, I thought
Robert was going to--

814
00:57:07,182 --> 00:57:08,015
- I see.

815
00:57:09,212 --> 00:57:12,315
Now I know why your husband
was so talkative this evening.

816
00:57:12,315 --> 00:57:14,198
It was all a plot.

817
00:57:14,198 --> 00:57:15,218
I always knew there was something

818
00:57:15,218 --> 00:57:17,941
wrong about the two of you.

819
00:57:17,941 --> 00:57:21,884
Well my dear, now you're
both going to prison.

820
00:57:21,884 --> 00:57:24,698
You and your dear husband.

821
00:57:24,698 --> 00:57:26,042
- No it was my idea,

822
00:57:26,042 --> 00:57:28,915
Robert doesn't know anything about this.

823
00:57:28,915 --> 00:57:31,224
- You gave him away yourself.

824
00:57:31,224 --> 00:57:33,354
Robert was going to, what?

825
00:57:33,354 --> 00:57:34,437
Keep me busy?

826
00:57:37,064 --> 00:57:41,685
You will send him to
jail with your own words.

827
00:57:41,685 --> 00:57:44,859
- No please, I'll do anything.

828
00:57:44,859 --> 00:57:46,762
- I'm gonna telephone the police.

829
00:57:46,762 --> 00:57:49,762
(suspenseful music)

830
00:57:55,933 --> 00:57:58,266
(screaming)

831
00:58:00,408 --> 00:58:03,741
(gasping and scuffling)

832
00:58:20,737 --> 00:58:21,737
- I'm sorry.

833
00:58:24,994 --> 00:58:26,634
Oh my God.

834
00:58:26,634 --> 00:58:27,467
Oh my God.

835
00:58:28,935 --> 00:58:31,768
(sobbing breaths)

836
00:58:53,646 --> 00:58:54,479
- Don't worry dear.

837
00:58:54,479 --> 00:58:56,844
(screaming)

838
00:58:56,844 --> 00:58:59,184
That part of it's over now.

839
00:58:59,184 --> 00:59:02,773
You posed a slightly different
problem from the others.

840
00:59:02,773 --> 00:59:04,773
All you wanted was love,

841
00:59:06,438 --> 00:59:09,574
but I always honor my end of the bargain,

842
00:59:09,574 --> 00:59:12,407
and of course I couldn't love you.

843
00:59:13,347 --> 00:59:16,273
So in order to get what I wanted,

844
00:59:16,273 --> 00:59:20,106
we had to resolve our
relationship, like this.

845
00:59:27,204 --> 00:59:29,293
- [Mrs. Albright] You see Mrs. Delaney,

846
00:59:29,293 --> 00:59:32,523
there are some things one shouldn't do.

847
00:59:32,523 --> 00:59:34,583
Not even for love.

848
00:59:34,583 --> 00:59:37,159
- I don't understand.

849
00:59:37,159 --> 00:59:39,327
- But you will my dear.

850
00:59:39,327 --> 00:59:40,160
You will.

851
00:59:41,125 --> 00:59:42,042
Come along.

852
00:59:42,883 --> 00:59:44,133
Come, come now.

853
00:59:46,067 --> 00:59:48,312
Give me your hand.

854
00:59:48,312 --> 00:59:49,145
You must.

855
00:59:50,492 --> 00:59:53,147
You see, you're mine now.

856
00:59:53,147 --> 00:59:56,147
(suspenseful music)

857
01:00:28,139 --> 01:00:30,389
(knocking)

858
01:00:37,967 --> 01:00:39,155
- Kathryn.

859
01:00:39,155 --> 01:00:40,626
Are you all right?

860
01:00:40,626 --> 01:00:42,459
- I was, I was asleep.

861
01:00:43,490 --> 01:00:47,133
- Kathryn listen to me,
we're alone in the house.

862
01:00:47,133 --> 01:00:49,446
- What's that sir, what did you say?

863
01:00:49,446 --> 01:00:51,121
- Mrs. Grove is gone.

864
01:00:51,121 --> 01:00:53,088
Her floor is covered with blood.

865
01:00:53,088 --> 01:00:57,098
No one's in Will's room or the
Delaney's or Miss Lester's.

866
01:00:57,098 --> 01:00:59,181
We're the only ones left.

867
01:01:00,379 --> 01:01:01,212
- Left?

868
01:01:01,212 --> 01:01:02,792
What do you mean?

869
01:01:02,792 --> 01:01:05,264
You said there's blood
in Aunt Mary's room?

870
01:01:05,264 --> 01:01:07,181
- And in Miss Lester's.

871
01:01:09,277 --> 01:01:11,871
- What about the new one?

872
01:01:11,871 --> 01:01:14,496
- I didn't try her room.

873
01:01:14,496 --> 01:01:15,446
Get dressed.

874
01:01:15,446 --> 01:01:16,497
Quickly.

875
01:01:16,497 --> 01:01:18,580
We're leaving this house.

876
01:01:21,590 --> 01:01:22,423
Now!

877
01:01:38,296 --> 01:01:39,296
Quickly now!

878
01:01:54,674 --> 01:01:56,007
Cover your eyes.

879
01:02:13,869 --> 01:02:15,037
- What is it?

880
01:02:15,037 --> 01:02:16,620
Why won't it break?

881
01:02:20,687 --> 01:02:21,520
- Kathryn.

882
01:02:22,618 --> 01:02:25,118
This is the work of the Devil,

883
01:02:26,658 --> 01:02:29,839
and I believe the Devil
is in this house tonight,

884
01:02:29,839 --> 01:02:32,256
or some servant of the Devil.

885
01:02:33,576 --> 01:02:35,285
- You mean Mrs. Albright?

886
01:02:35,285 --> 01:02:36,118
- Yes?

887
01:02:41,295 --> 01:02:45,295
No no, Kathryn dear our
kind invented the cross.

888
01:02:48,070 --> 01:02:50,259
- Where are the others?

889
01:02:50,259 --> 01:02:51,092
- With me.

890
01:02:52,116 --> 01:02:56,070
It's a bit of a disappointment
really how easy it was.

891
01:02:56,070 --> 01:02:57,548
- Why have you come here?

892
01:02:57,548 --> 01:02:59,127
Why choose us?

893
01:02:59,127 --> 01:03:01,468
- It's a kind of a test really.

894
01:03:01,468 --> 01:03:02,394
For me.

895
01:03:02,394 --> 01:03:04,127
Not for you.

896
01:03:04,127 --> 01:03:06,371
My master sets me a challenge.

897
01:03:06,371 --> 01:03:10,334
Can I win the souls of
everyone in a house?

898
01:03:10,334 --> 01:03:12,590
- But you haven't won ours yet.

899
01:03:12,590 --> 01:03:13,757
- No, not yet.

900
01:03:15,778 --> 01:03:20,084
Of course almost always
somebody catches on,

901
01:03:20,084 --> 01:03:22,866
and that usually makes it more difficult.

902
01:03:22,866 --> 01:03:25,273
I knew from the first moment I saw you

903
01:03:25,273 --> 01:03:27,606
that you would be a problem,

904
01:03:28,573 --> 01:03:31,156
but we will do the best we can.

905
01:03:33,363 --> 01:03:36,030
(ominous music)

906
01:03:40,072 --> 01:03:41,943
- Still pretending to limp?

907
01:03:41,943 --> 01:03:44,508
Why bother, we know what you are.

908
01:03:44,508 --> 01:03:46,675
- Oh no, the limp is real.

909
01:03:47,841 --> 01:03:49,563
An old war wound.

910
01:03:49,563 --> 01:03:50,693
- War wound?

911
01:03:50,693 --> 01:03:51,526
What war?

912
01:03:53,564 --> 01:03:55,564
- Why our war of course.

913
01:04:00,638 --> 01:04:01,618
- [Kathryn] Oh God!

914
01:04:01,618 --> 01:04:03,201
- Kathryn, Kathryn!

915
01:04:12,878 --> 01:04:14,697
Stop it, stop it!

916
01:04:14,697 --> 01:04:15,761
Kathryn stop it!

917
01:04:15,761 --> 01:04:17,641
- Jesus she's going to kill us!

918
01:04:17,641 --> 01:04:20,170
- No, no, that isn't what she wants.

919
01:04:20,170 --> 01:04:22,079
Please Kathryn you must listen!

920
01:04:22,079 --> 01:04:25,476
She wants something far more
valuable than our lives.

921
01:04:25,476 --> 01:04:28,332
She wants our souls do you understand?

922
01:04:28,332 --> 01:04:29,165
- Our souls?

923
01:04:29,165 --> 01:04:29,998
- Yes.

924
01:04:29,998 --> 01:04:33,139
To be with her forever in Hell.

925
01:04:33,139 --> 01:04:33,993
- No!

926
01:04:33,993 --> 01:04:35,243
- Listen to me!

927
01:04:36,175 --> 01:04:39,480
She can not take our souls
unless we surrender them.

928
01:04:39,480 --> 01:04:41,063
We must resist her.

929
01:04:41,966 --> 01:04:44,549
Kathryn, do you fear the Devil?

930
01:04:46,265 --> 01:04:47,674
- I don't know!

931
01:04:47,674 --> 01:04:48,915
- Well you must know!

932
01:04:48,915 --> 01:04:50,628
What use is your life if you buy it

933
01:04:50,628 --> 01:04:52,554
with an eternity in Hell?

934
01:04:52,554 --> 01:04:56,721
- I'm sorry sir, I'm sorry I
just don't know, I don't know!

935
01:04:57,916 --> 01:04:59,416
I don't wanna die.

936
01:05:01,635 --> 01:05:05,052
(book clatters on floor)

937
01:05:07,261 --> 01:05:09,678
(whimpering)

938
01:05:15,102 --> 01:05:16,730
(yells in surprise)

939
01:05:16,730 --> 01:05:17,721
What is it?

940
01:05:17,721 --> 01:05:19,078
- I don't know.

941
01:05:19,078 --> 01:05:20,745
One of her servants.

942
01:05:21,648 --> 01:05:24,528
(screaming)

943
01:05:24,528 --> 01:05:26,111
There, there it is!

944
01:05:27,578 --> 01:05:31,745
(dramatic music)
(whimpering)

945
01:05:38,927 --> 01:05:41,260
(screaming)

946
01:05:43,945 --> 01:05:45,448
- It's still alive!

947
01:05:45,448 --> 01:05:47,781
(screaming)

948
01:05:53,375 --> 01:05:55,782
(glass shatters)

949
01:05:55,782 --> 01:05:59,532
- You're gonna have to
pay for that Mr. Gray.

950
01:06:06,090 --> 01:06:09,507
(sobbing and whimpering)

951
01:06:17,267 --> 01:06:19,767
In number five, in Hell alive,

952
01:06:20,677 --> 01:06:23,177
thy souls forever in my hands.

953
01:06:24,965 --> 01:06:27,132
So go and do as I command.

954
01:06:28,646 --> 01:06:31,646
(suspenseful music)

955
01:06:49,908 --> 01:06:52,241
(screaming)

956
01:06:59,428 --> 01:07:01,011
- Kathryn, candles.

957
01:07:02,232 --> 01:07:04,024
We need candles.

958
01:07:04,024 --> 01:07:05,644
- That drawer.

959
01:07:05,644 --> 01:07:06,477
- Ow!

960
01:07:09,710 --> 01:07:13,877
(whimpering)
(suspenseful music)

961
01:07:16,704 --> 01:07:18,804
Whatever happens remember,

962
01:07:18,804 --> 01:07:23,443
God doesn't ask anything
of us that we can't do.

963
01:07:23,443 --> 01:07:24,776
- It's too late.

964
01:07:25,707 --> 01:07:26,540
Too late.

965
01:07:29,009 --> 01:07:31,807
(screaming)

966
01:07:31,807 --> 01:07:35,974
(stabbing)
(yelling in pain)

967
01:07:42,004 --> 01:07:44,171
(hissing)

968
01:07:47,647 --> 01:07:49,278
- This way Kathryn.

969
01:07:49,278 --> 01:07:52,278
(suspenseful music)

970
01:07:58,658 --> 01:08:02,075
(screaming and laughter)

971
01:08:04,200 --> 01:08:06,867
(yells in pain)

972
01:08:16,874 --> 01:08:19,707
(stairs creaking)

973
01:08:32,876 --> 01:08:34,250
- Well surely you didn't expect

974
01:08:34,250 --> 01:08:37,583
something civilized from me did you Sam?

975
01:08:38,617 --> 01:08:40,978
- The Lord is my shepherd
I shall not want.

976
01:08:40,978 --> 01:08:43,600
He maketh me to lie
down in green pastures.

977
01:08:43,600 --> 01:08:46,980
- See that I'm the one who's
making you lie down now.

978
01:08:46,980 --> 01:08:48,353
- He restoreth my soul--

979
01:08:48,353 --> 01:08:52,869
- Oh yes yes yes, but what
about the girl's soul?

980
01:08:52,869 --> 01:08:54,102
- The girl?

981
01:08:54,102 --> 01:08:55,075
(laughter)

982
01:08:55,075 --> 01:08:57,412
- That got your attention didn't it?

983
01:08:57,412 --> 01:08:58,995
Better take a look.

984
01:09:05,832 --> 01:09:09,832
She's in need of some of
your spiritual comfort.

985
01:09:16,890 --> 01:09:18,973
(crying)

986
01:09:20,994 --> 01:09:22,744
- God please help me!

987
01:09:27,821 --> 01:09:29,698
- Don't look away!

988
01:09:29,698 --> 01:09:31,934
If everything works out the way you hope,

989
01:09:31,934 --> 01:09:34,078
we'll have a martyr here.

990
01:09:34,078 --> 01:09:35,514
- She's innocent!

991
01:09:35,514 --> 01:09:37,355
She doesn't deserve this!

992
01:09:37,355 --> 01:09:39,551
- God please make it stop!

993
01:09:39,551 --> 01:09:41,383
Make it stop!

994
01:09:41,383 --> 01:09:42,741
(screaming)

995
01:09:42,741 --> 01:09:45,163
God please make it stop!

996
01:09:45,163 --> 01:09:47,496
(screaming)

997
01:09:50,509 --> 01:09:52,558
- What will you give me?

998
01:09:52,558 --> 01:09:54,078
- Don't answer her!

999
01:09:54,078 --> 01:09:55,811
Don't answer her!

1000
01:09:55,811 --> 01:09:59,061
- Now Sam, let's be realistic shall we?

1001
01:10:01,306 --> 01:10:04,042
Kathryn's a nice dull sort of girl,

1002
01:10:04,042 --> 01:10:07,628
but we both know she isn't
cut from the martyr cloth.

1003
01:10:07,628 --> 01:10:09,403
Maybe you'll be able to endure

1004
01:10:09,403 --> 01:10:13,570
but as for Kathryn, I'd give
her another 10 or 15 minutes.

1005
01:10:16,063 --> 01:10:17,896
- Oh God make it stop!

1006
01:10:19,141 --> 01:10:22,118
- My dear, if you want little Miss Lester

1007
01:10:22,118 --> 01:10:26,757
to stop her games you'll
have to ask someone closer.

1008
01:10:26,757 --> 01:10:28,674
- Please make her stop.

1009
01:10:30,263 --> 01:10:32,096
- What'll you give me?

1010
01:10:32,988 --> 01:10:35,609
- Anything, anything please!

1011
01:10:35,609 --> 01:10:36,442
- Done.

1012
01:10:36,442 --> 01:10:37,275
- No!

1013
01:10:49,626 --> 01:10:52,043
- Hmm, not even five minutes.

1014
01:10:53,245 --> 01:10:54,945
(clucks tongue)

1015
01:10:54,945 --> 01:10:56,631
Is the human soul growing weaker

1016
01:10:56,631 --> 01:10:59,097
or is it that people simply
can't stand suffering

1017
01:10:59,097 --> 01:11:00,847
the way they used to?

1018
01:11:02,250 --> 01:11:04,001
Come my dear.

1019
01:11:04,001 --> 01:11:05,663
You've made a fool's bargain,

1020
01:11:05,663 --> 01:11:08,346
but then fools often do don't they?

1021
01:11:08,346 --> 01:11:09,179
- Wait.

1022
01:11:10,151 --> 01:11:12,296
I'll make a trade.

1023
01:11:12,296 --> 01:11:13,713
My soul for hers.

1024
01:11:15,642 --> 01:11:16,642
- Oh really?

1025
01:11:17,664 --> 01:11:20,321
Well you certainly think
highly of yourself.

1026
01:11:20,321 --> 01:11:22,071
- Don't play with me!

1027
01:11:23,021 --> 01:11:25,021
You'll make the bargain.

1028
01:11:26,596 --> 01:11:30,263
- No, that would be too
generous on my part.

1029
01:11:31,609 --> 01:11:36,255
If I let her go who knows
what she may do with her life.

1030
01:11:36,255 --> 01:11:40,066
She might become a notorious sinner.

1031
01:11:40,066 --> 01:11:42,068
Would you expect us to deprive ourselves

1032
01:11:42,068 --> 01:11:44,858
of the pleasure of her
company in that event?

1033
01:11:44,858 --> 01:11:46,191
No, it won't do.

1034
01:11:48,966 --> 01:11:51,519
Can we limit the bargain?

1035
01:11:51,519 --> 01:11:53,436
Be a bit more specific?

1036
01:11:54,622 --> 01:11:57,539
- You release her, no more torture.

1037
01:11:59,229 --> 01:12:01,417
You don't visit her again.

1038
01:12:01,417 --> 01:12:03,667
Offer her no more bargains.

1039
01:12:05,492 --> 01:12:08,159
She leaves alive unbound by you.

1040
01:12:10,699 --> 01:12:12,116
Her soul her own.

1041
01:12:14,277 --> 01:12:18,444
Whatever evil she may do after
that, that is on her soul.

1042
01:12:21,071 --> 01:12:23,225
- No more torture.

1043
01:12:23,225 --> 01:12:25,757
I refrain from killing her.

1044
01:12:25,757 --> 01:12:29,097
I erase the bargain we just made.

1045
01:12:29,097 --> 01:12:31,802
She's free to go where she wishes,

1046
01:12:31,802 --> 01:12:35,232
and I offer her no new bargains.

1047
01:12:35,232 --> 01:12:38,339
In return, you give me your soul

1048
01:12:38,339 --> 01:12:42,172
to be lost in my master's
shadow for all time.

1049
01:12:44,715 --> 01:12:46,244
- Yes.

1050
01:12:46,244 --> 01:12:47,077
- Done!

1051
01:12:53,300 --> 01:12:55,883
I knew your weakness all along.

1052
01:12:56,986 --> 01:12:58,429
- What weakness?

1053
01:12:58,429 --> 01:12:59,895
- Hubris.

1054
01:12:59,895 --> 01:13:03,162
You thought you could
redeem the soul of another.

1055
01:13:03,162 --> 01:13:06,862
Do you really imagine
yourself to be the redeemer?

1056
01:13:06,862 --> 01:13:10,112
Girl the door's open go where you will.

1057
01:13:24,415 --> 01:13:26,498
- Go on, don't look back.

1058
01:13:28,944 --> 01:13:31,611
(ominous music)

1059
01:13:38,722 --> 01:13:41,004
- Have you finished the book my dear?

1060
01:13:41,004 --> 01:13:42,169
- Yes.

1061
01:13:42,169 --> 01:13:43,372
It told me what to do.

1062
01:13:43,372 --> 01:13:45,671
It told me everything.

1063
01:13:45,671 --> 01:13:47,866
It was just like the book said.

1064
01:13:47,866 --> 01:13:51,616
It didn't hurt at all,
but I pretended it did.

1065
01:13:51,616 --> 01:13:54,381
- You were simply marvelous.

1066
01:13:54,381 --> 01:13:55,214
- Kathryn?

1067
01:13:56,905 --> 01:13:59,655
- Yes, I always keep my promises.

1068
01:14:01,022 --> 01:14:02,803
She's free to go where she wishes,

1069
01:14:02,803 --> 01:14:06,386
but she had already
chosen to come with me,

1070
01:14:08,228 --> 01:14:10,482
and I need make no new bargains

1071
01:14:10,482 --> 01:14:13,815
because our bargain had already been made.

1072
01:14:13,815 --> 01:14:15,398
- It's all in here.

1073
01:14:16,469 --> 01:14:19,429
All about the Earth King, and
how he'll make you powerful

1074
01:14:19,429 --> 01:14:22,148
so you can get back at your enemies.

1075
01:14:22,148 --> 01:14:24,159
- Am I your enemy?

1076
01:14:24,159 --> 01:14:26,589
- A friend is someone who can help you.

1077
01:14:26,589 --> 01:14:27,785
You couldn't.

1078
01:14:27,785 --> 01:14:28,618
She could.

1079
01:14:29,675 --> 01:14:33,787
- But let's be completely
fair about this now shall we?

1080
01:14:33,787 --> 01:14:36,200
You can read now can't you Kathryn?

1081
01:14:36,200 --> 01:14:37,172
- Yes.

1082
01:14:37,172 --> 01:14:39,859
- And you have already
tasted my knowledge.

1083
01:14:39,859 --> 01:14:41,197
- Yes.

1084
01:14:41,197 --> 01:14:44,434
- Do you accept me of your own free will?

1085
01:14:44,434 --> 01:14:45,267
- Kathryn!

1086
01:14:46,578 --> 01:14:48,197
- Yes.

1087
01:14:48,197 --> 01:14:51,463
- Do you give yourself to
me of your own free will?

1088
01:14:51,463 --> 01:14:52,300
- [Kathryn] Yes.

1089
01:14:52,300 --> 01:14:56,443
- Then the deal is done,
and I have kept my word.

1090
01:14:56,443 --> 01:14:59,443
(suspenseful music)

1091
01:15:02,551 --> 01:15:03,468
- You fool.

1092
